##The surface "anti-epidemic" , secretly collect money, eggshells freely staged Loot a burning house drama

Micro Signal Xincaijing

Function introduction, the recorder of new business, the promoter of New Economy.

-- Hung Fei Chow
Edited by gale

According to Zinccaijing, since January 31, many homeowners in Wuhan, Beijing, Hangzhou and Shenzhen who have signed contracts with eggshell apartments have received official "New Year greetings" calls from Eggshell, and have been informed that, due to the impact of the epidemic, they have responded to the national call, to waive a certain amount of rent.

Before he could answer the call, the caller had already hung up, and either the line was busy or no one answered.

Meanwhile, eggshell has posted a "rent refund policy" on its official Weibo Account, which says it will offer a one-month rent refund to tenants in Wuhan, at the same time for the other city tenants in accordance with the extension of the time to return the corresponding number of days rent.

"Rent Refund Policy" on the official Weibo of eggshell apartment

However, most of the tenants do not know about this, but some people pay rent only after the know about it, call customer service calls to inquire unsuccessfully.

For a while, the practice of "eating two ends of an egg shell apartment" was "sent" to Weibo during protests by landlords and tenants.

As promised, freedom was also exposed two days ago during the outbreak of tenants inconvenient to move to rent, arbitrarily bid up the rent. This news, although the official explanation, but still in many at ease under the anger of renters, let it after the shell boarded the hot search.

Feel Free CEO Xiong Lin on "rent hike" friends circle explanation, picture source network

In this way, the eggshell apartment and free left hand to do "public good" to fight the epidemic, but the right hand to put money into their own pockets, in this series of fancy operation quietly issued a "national disaster wealth.

But it was the landlords and tenants who were most affected by the outbreak who ended up paying the bill.

Rent-free for those who are notified

"eggshell called and said it was a tough call to waive my three-month rent to compensate tenants who could not return because of the outbreak. "

"I was just angry and overwhelmed, " Ms. Nie told Zinccaijing.

The reason for this mood, because this rent is very important to her. After getting her monthly rent, Ms. Nie had to use her salary to subsidize some of her monthly mortgage payments. More importantly, if the rent was waived, it would mean that she would not receive a penny for the next three months.

In response, Ms. Nie called Eggshell Customer Service several times, but was always told to wait in line. She had no choice but to file a complaint with some government platforms in Wuhan, "If the eggshells don't pay me rent after the epidemic is over, I will choose to call the police, " Ms. Nie said.

The conversation between the owner and the eggshell apartment

In fact, such experiences not only happen to Wuhan homeowners like Ms. Nie, but also to many homeowners in Beijing and Hangzhou.

Ms. Wang, a Beijing homeowner, also received a call from the eggshell apartment on Feb. 4, saying it was vacant due to the "force majeure" of the outbreak and would be spared a month's rent.

Hearing this, Ms. Wang immediately expressed her disagreement, but did not wait for her to finish saying that the other party had already hung up the phone. "I was really angry, which meant I had to do it with or without consent, " she said, before learning that her house was not vacant.

So Ms. Wang called the Shell's customer service number again. "either the line was busy all the time, or she hung up after all kinds of prevarication. " At the time, many landlords were already online reporting and complaining about the Shell apartment, it means that the eggshell apartment is in a "routine" , as if it is a bad idea to rent-free and cheat the owner, and has been trending on Weibo.

EGGSHELL apartment may be to maintain stability, on February 7 to the nation's homeowners sent a mass text message, the content of the message said: for the recent spread of eggshell apartment "Tao Lu landlord" rumors are pure rumors, please do not believe rumors.

The content of the text message sent by the interviewee, source of the interviewee

Like other homeowners, Ms. Sha, the Hangzhou owner, received the text message. "I felt like I was eating a fly when I saw this text, " she said, because she had also received a phone call from the eggshell earlier, which included a rent-free notice, he also told me that the rent would be paid a month late.

In this regard, zinc finance immediately to a number of landlords for verification, the final response is consistent.

In addition, according to Zinccaijing, there are many homeowners did not receive the eggshell phone, was directly exempted from the rent. "If I hadn't told my sister, she wouldn't know about the rent-free thing and would be waiting for the rent. "

However, let these owners even more unexpected is that they were forced to give these "love" , and not really implemented to the tenants.

On the contrary, the tenants are still paying out.

Harvest in "relief" and "price increase" 

For the tenants of the "harvest" , the eggshell apartment and freedom can be said to have played a "good abacus.

On Feb. 3, eggshell's official Weibo account posted an update on a "renter's rent refund policy, " which said it would offer targeted subsidies to tenants who could not return to Wuhan and other cities. At the same time, it also launched the policy in its APP.

"Rent relief notice for tenants" on the home page of the eggshell apartment APP

However, interviews with Zinccaijing revealed that most tenants said they were unaware of the policy and had received a prompt text message from the Shell "on time" and paid their rent.

Obumi is such a tenant, "February 3 I received a reminder message, after paying rent to listen to friends said that this plan, " Obumi told Zinccaijing. She told Zinccaijing that she had signed a lease because she liked the way the eggshells were decorated, and that it was nice to live there until the outbreak made sense of the company.

As soon as she learned about the return policy, she applied, only to find that she had to wait until the 10th to apply. So Obumi applied again on the morning of the 10th, and the application was successful, but the rent would not be paid until March 2nd.

However, just as Obumi was about to close the page, he found the lowermost of the policy's fine print, which read "return rent (except monthly payments) " . "after reading the fine print, I realized I couldn't use the returned rent in a rental way, which really pissed me off. "

Hidden limits in policy, source

In response, Zinccaijing confirmed that an eggshell insider, he said the return of rent is not applicable to the monthly rental deduction, can only be used to offset other costs. This means that the rent refund is an invisible limit for most egg shell renters who choose to pay monthly.

Li Yuan was also a tenant who fell in front of the restrictions.

"If it wasn't for the rent-back policy on the APP, I wouldn't have seen it this year, " she said. After several applications, she was "disqualified. ".

To add insult to injury, after talking to the eggshell housekeeper, she was told that if you pay monthly, both the service fee and the rent will go up, while the annual fee will not go up. "This is to encourage me to pay more money, then simply choose the monthly pay, big or small more money, and so on to find a good house to move away. " Li Yuan said.

Interview notes with Eggshell Butler, source

Alex Fong was in the same boat when it came to renewing the lease, but the company was comfortable.

Alex Fong, a self sufficient renter in Beijing, had planned to change her apartment when it expired in February, but could not return because of the epidemic, so she had to renew it. Also, in a conversation with her housekeeper, she learned that if she were to renew it now, the rent would rise by 3 percent.

As for the reasons for the rent increase, the housekeeper explained that "the new price is set according to the market" , this statement can also be seen in the free customer service there. But in Beijing, for example, the average monthly rent was 82.84 yuan per square meter in January, up 1.68 percent from the previous month but down 2.9 percent from January last year, according to data from Linjia.

Feel free to respond to customer service "rent increases, " the source of respondents

That said, the free wave of rent increases is unreasonable.

In the end, though, Xiao Fang chose to renew the lease. "At that time, I felt that I was in a financial crisis, but I had no choice. It was unrealistic to look for a house at this time. I could only continue to sign the contract for one month, " Xiao Fang said to Zinccaijing helplessly.

From the eggshell apartment notice owners rent-free, and then free, eggshell on the tenant's "double harvest" , this is a complete set of "national calamity wealth" charges. In addition to anger and frustration, some homeowners and renters are also thinking about the question:

Is it true that the two companies are doing this in the midst of an epidemic?

Two ostriches with a bad taste

"when an ostrich is in danger, it buries its head in the ground so that it thinks it is out of danger. "

This phenomenon was first mentioned in the journal Nature and is now generally used as a metaphor for people or things that deceive themselves. At this point, the eggshell apartment and the ease of two ostriches with their heads in the dirt.

Since the incident to the online public opinion ferment, the two parents rented apartment officials basically did not make any decent explanation and attitude. Although free CEO Xiong Lin explained the rent increase in his friends'circle on February 10, and synced the explanation to his micro blog, the tenant said he didn't accept it and quickly deleted it, and then there's no explanation.

The official eggshell is cleaner than the free-flowing kind. Open eggshell's official Weibo account and you can see that the most recent post was dated Feb. 10 and has not been explained since.

Eggshell apartments and the free official Weibo photo source network

In this way, the two ostriches buried their heads in the ground, even if the public opinion how to go, all seem to have nothing to do with them, and showed a "I do, you can do what to me? " Attitude.

The question arises: Why would eggshell, which went public on the Nasdaq on Jan. 27, make such a risky move at a time when it is the head company on the track as a long term rental apartment?

Perhaps the answer can be found in the listing prospectus for eggshell apartments.

Eggshell's revenue was positive for the first nine months of 2017 to 2019, according to the prospectus, but losses were also present. The Prospectus showed a net loss of RMB2.516 bn for the first nine months of 2019, compared with RMB813M for the same period in 2018.

There is also a place to be aware that in 2017,2018 and the first nine months of 2019,91.3 per cent, 75.8 per cent and 65.7 per cent of eggshell tenants used a "rent loan" , according to the prospectus.

This means that the main revenue of eggshell apartments is from "rent loan" , and the "rent loan" of the harm, in fact, from last year have a thunderstorm in the long rental apartment brand can be seen in the thunderstorm.

As a result, in December last year, six ministries and commissions issued "opinions on rectifying and standardizing the order of the housing rental market, " requiring that the amount of housing rental loans should not exceed 30 percent of the rental income of housing rental enterprises. From the prospectus of the data, eggshell apartment "rent" ratio far beyond the national "red line" standard.

So while eggshell apartments are on the market, there are still plenty of holes that need to be filled, as they showed earlier this year.

In January of this year, the pulse of someone exposed the eggshell apartment suspected disguised layoffs, employees pay only Beijing's minimum standard of 1,500 yuan. For this matter, zinc finance to the shell apartment of the internal verification, the other side said that there is no such thing.

This is already the case for eggshells. Although the percentage of "rent loans" is not as high as that for eggshells, last year they were caught up in public opinion such as "formaldehyde houses" and "black intermediaries" , so life may not be any better than the eggshell apartment.

But even that is no reason for the two companies to be so unappetizing. "fighting the epidemic should be something that all members of society should do, and it is very unreasonable for people like eggshell apartments and ease to focus on commercial interests instead of social responsibility during this period, " Fang Xiaoqi, a real estate industry analyst, told Zncaijing.

So far, many homeowners and renters say they are working to assert their rights to eggshell apartments and their ability to "get the money and not react" . Homeowners in Beijing, Wuhan and Hangzhou have set up rights groups and are ready to take legal action, according to Zinccaijing.

Eggshell apartment landlord rights group, photo source respondents

Although it is impossible to predict the final outcome of this event, it is certain that the image of eggshell apartments and ease in the minds of consumers has been lost. For both companies, the original sin may have been to forget the fact:

"water can carry a boat, also can overturn a boat" this sentence, also apply to consumers and companies.

(Ms. Wang, Ms. Sha, Obumi, Li Yuan and Xiao Fang were all pseudonyms, at the request of the interviewee.)
